If Gabinius and Piso left Rome before the tribuni plebis entered on their office, Cicero's narrative will be in order, for he might say that this year was really over when the two consuls left Rome for their provinces, though the first of January had not come. Cicero’s narrative ought to mean that the consuls left Rome before the end of the year.
